    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36.47"/>
                
                <note>ans. 5/25/72</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">47</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    Sanford
                    Lancaster Pike
                    Hockessin, 
                    Delaware   19707
   
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I have just finished reading your book <hi rend="underline">Black Elk Speaks</hi>, and I am sincerely moved by its beauty. I've read many other boooks of this sort lately, but they've all been so worked over that they've become sterilized. Your book, Black Elk's life, really lives, and I feel it has given me a greater understanding of what Indian life was. I thank-you for the book.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Beth Taylor</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    HOCKESSIN, DE MAY 19 1972 A.M. 19707
                </ab>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>8 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>8¢ EISENHOWER∙USA</p>
                </figure>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine><unclear/>r. John <hi rend="caps">D.<sic>G.</sic></hi> Neihardt</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine><unclear cert="high">P</unclear>oet Laureate of Nebraska</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine><del><unclear>T</unclear>he Capitol Building</del> <add>5835 Vine St.</add></addrLine> 
                        <addrLine><unclear cert="high">L</unclear>incoln, Nebraska</addrLine> 
                    </address>
                </ab>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    Taylor 
                    Sanford 
                    Lancaster Pike 
                    Hockessin, Delaware 19707
                </ab>
                
